paragraphs.title: HTML Display
GoogleVis: Bar Chart
paragraphs.text:
%livy.sparkr

# Workaround for Spark issue with googleVis: SPARK-23780
detach("package:SparkR")
library(googleVis)
suppressPackageStartupMessages(library(SparkR))

df=data.frame(country=c("US", "GB", "BR"), 
              val1=c(10,13,14), 
              val2=c(23,12,32))
Bar <- gvisBarChart(df)
cat("%html ", Bar$html$chart)

paragraphs.title: GoogleVis: Line chart
paragraphs.text:
%livy.sparkr

# Workaround for Spark issue with googleVis: SPARK-23780
detach("package:SparkR")
library(googleVis)
suppressPackageStartupMessages(library(SparkR))

df=data.frame(country=c("US", "GB", "BR"), 
              val1=c(10,13,14), 
              val2=c(23,12,32))

Line <- gvisLineChart(df)

cat("%html ", Line$html$chart)

%livy.sparkr
library(ggplot2)
pres_rating <- data.frame(
  rating = as.numeric(presidents),
  year = as.numeric(floor(time(presidents))),
  quarter = as.numeric(cycle(presidents))
)
p <- ggplot(pres_rating, aes(x=year, y=quarter, fill=rating))
plot(p + geom_raster())

paragraphs.title: GoogleViz: Bubble Chart
paragraphs.text:
%livy.sparkr

# Workaround for Spark issue with googleVis: SPARK-23780
detach("package:SparkR")
library(googleVis)
suppressPackageStartupMessages(library(SparkR))

bubble <- gvisBubbleChart(Fruits, idvar="Fruit", 
                          xvar="Sales", yvar="Expenses",
                          colorvar="Year", sizevar="Profit",
                          options=list(
                            hAxis='{minValue:75, maxValue:125}'))
cat("%html ", bubble$html$chart)

paragraphs.title: GoogleViz: Geo Chart
paragraphs.text:
%livy.sparkr

# Workaround for Spark issue with googleVis: SPARK-23780
detach("package:SparkR")
library(googleVis)
suppressPackageStartupMessages(library(SparkR))

geo = gvisGeoChart(Exports, locationvar = "Country", colorvar="Profit", options=list(Projection = "kavrayskiy-vii"))
cat("%html ", geo$html$chart)
